{"KISH":[{"def":"A workman's name for the graphite which forms incidentally in iron smelting.","pos":""}],"KISS":[{"def":"To salute with the lips, as a mark of affection, reverence, submission, forgiveness, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"To touch gently, as if fondly or caressingly.","pos":""}],"KISSING BUG":[{"def":"Any one of several species of blood-sucking, venomous Hemiptera that sometimes bite the lip or other parts of the human body, causing painful sores, as the cone-nose (Conorhinus sanguisuga).","pos":""}],"KISSING STRINGS":[{"def":"Cap or bonnet strings made long to tie under the chin.","pos":""}],"KISSINGCRUST":[{"def":"The portion of the upper crust of a loaf which has touched another loaf in baking.","pos":""}],"KIST":[{"def":"A chest; hence, a coffin.","pos":""}],"KISTVAEN":[{"def":"A Celtic monument, commonly known as a dolmen.","pos":""}]}